        <div type="bibliography" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>
            <bibl><ptr target="#IDodoneDVC"/> <citedRange>4</citedRange></bibl> (<bibl><ptr target="#Chaniotis2017"/>, <citedRange>56</citedRange></bibl> [new interpretation]; <bibl><ptr target="#NietoIzquierdo2019"/>, <citedRange>113</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="#GartziouTatti2020"/>, <citedRange>§ 17 note 58</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="#CIOD"/> <citedRange>4</citedRange></bibl> [last consulted 14/08/2025]).
            </p>
            <p>Cf.    
            <bibl><ptr target="#Chaniotis2013"/>, <citedRange>206</citedRange></bibl> (legal matters); <bibl><ptr target="#Katsadima2017"/>, <citedRange>132 notes 14-15 and 135, note 63</citedRange></bibl> (enquiries by women); <bibl><ptr target="#Frank2024"/>, <citedRange>108</citedRange></bibl> (enquiries by women); <bibl><ptr target="#MéndezDosuna2024"/></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="#Parker2015"/>, <citedRange>213</citedRange>.</bibl>
            </p>
        </div>
        <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc">
            <div type="textpart" subtype="face" n="A">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><rs type="deity" ref="#theos"><w lemma="θεός">θεὸς</w></rs> <rs type="deity" ref="#tyche"><w lemma="τύχα">τύχα</w></rs>  <pc>:</pc> <persName><name nymRef="#Γνέφας">Γνέφας</name></persName> <pc>:</pc> <persName><name nymRef="#Ἀνάγυλλα">Ἀνάγυλλα</name></persName>  
                    <lb n="2"/><persName><name nymRef="#Σίβυλλα">Σίβυλλα</name></persName> <pc>:</pc> <rs type="verb_question">ἐπερωτοντι</rs> τὸν <rs type="deity" ref="#Zeus"><rs type="deity" ref="#theos"><w lemma="θεός">θεὸν</w></rs></rs>
                    <lb n="3"/><rs type="conditional_conjunction">αἰ</rs> τὰ δίκαια μαστεύοντι ταύ
                    <lb n="4" break="no"/>ταν νικῆν περὶ θἠματίο <space quantity="3" unit="character" cert="medium"/>
                </ab>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            <app loc="1">
                <lem resp="#IDodoneDVC">Γνέφας <note>Curbera apud</note></lem>
                <rdg resp="#IDodoneDVC">γνέφας</rdg>
                <rdg resp="#CIOD">Γνεφᾶς</rdg>
            </app>
            <app loc="2">
                <lem resp="#CIOD">σίβυλλα <note>Carbon apud</note></lem>
            </app>        
             <app loc="3-4">
                <lem resp="#NietoIzquierdo2019">ταῦτα|{ν}</lem>
             </app>        
        </div>    
        <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>God. Fortune. Gnephas, Anagylla, Sibylla ask the god: in case they pursue legal claims, let this woman win about the garment.</p>
        </div>
        <div type="commentary" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">  
            <p>This private enquiry belongs to the well attested category of consultations to the oracle on <rs type="theme" ref="#justice">judicial matters</rs>, although neither the specific issue, regarding a garment, or the opposite party are mentioned. The number of persons involved in the dispute and the syntactical interpretation of the text, also present difficulties.</p>           
            <p>The number of enquirers varies according to the different interpretations of <foreign xml:lang="grc">ΓΝΕΦΑΣ</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="grc">ΣΙΒΥΛΛΑ</foreign> as common or personal names, so they are three following Curbera’s interpretation (a man, Gnephas, and two women, Anagylla and Sibylla), but two according to DVC editors (two women, Anagylla and Sibylla, <foreign xml:lang="grc">γνέφας</foreign> being the wool product used for handicrafts, cf. Gartziou-Tatti) and CIOD (a man, Gnephas, and a woman, Anagylla, <foreign xml:lang="grc">σίβυλλα</foreign> being the religious title of Anagylla).</p>   

<p>According to Chaniotis, the pronoun <foreign xml:lang="grc">ταῦταν</foreign> (ll. 3-4) refers to <foreign xml:lang="grc">δέλτος</foreign>, so this is a mention of a token to be drawn (on cleromancy in Dodona cf. <bibl><ptr target="#Parker2015"/>, <citedRange>213</citedRange></bibl>). On the contrary, Nieto Izquierdo corrects <foreign xml:lang="grc">ταῦταν</foreign> into <foreign xml:lang="grc">ταῦτα</foreign>, with spurious nu. Alternatively, <foreign xml:lang="grc">ταῦταν</foreign> can refer to the last personal name, <foreign xml:lang="grc">Σίβυλλα</foreign>, who might be the principal instigator of the judicial process. In any case, the construction with the infinitive remains asyndetic and the resulting phrasing is closer to a request to the god than to an actual question to the oracle.</p>   

            <p><emph>Ithaca's results</emph>: <ref target="https://dodonaonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/IDodone_Online_4_Ithaca.html">Results</ref>, <ref target="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/IDodone/IDodoneOnline/refs/heads/main/ithaca-results/IDodone_Online_4.md">Metadata</ref></p>
        </div>
